<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-24T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-24T10:00:00-05:00" n="744" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.52/116b: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Third Secretary of Embassy in
                                    Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-24T11:00:00-04:00">September 24, 1936—11
                                        a.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>135. In view of apparently reliable press reports, you should
                                withdraw from Madrid at once unless some imperative duty compels you
                                to remain. This withdrawal should include Johnson<note n="49" xml:id="d744fn49">John D. Johnson, Consul at Madrid.</note> and
                                all American staff. War Department states this withdrawal should
                                also include Col. Fuqua.<note n="50" xml:id="d744fn50">Col. Stephen
                                    O. Fuqna, Military Attaché in Spain.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>